Let's use the principle of inclusion-exclusion to solve this problem. Suppose \(A\) is the set of people who brought yoga mats, \(B\) is the set of people who brought water bottles, and \(|A|\) and \(|B|\) denote the number of elements in sets \(A\) and \(B\), respectively.  By the principle of inclusion-exclusion, we have
\begin{align*}|A\cup B| &= |A| + |B| - |A\cap B|\\ &= 36+26-20\\ &= 42.\end{align*}
We know that there are 42 people in the class, and therefore 42 people had either a yoga mat, a water bottle, or both.  This must mean that no one had to suffer through class not having a yoga mat or a water bottle. \<answer>0</answer>

