response:
Now,
\begin{align*}
M &= 3x^2 + 10xy + 3y^2 - x^2 - y^2 + 1\\
&= (3x^2 + 10xy + 3y^2) - (x^2 + y^2) + 1\\
&= (3x + 3y)(x + y) - (x^2 + y^2) + 1.
\end{align*}
From the second equation, let's calculate the value of $(3x + 3y)(x + y) - (x^2 + y^2).$
\begin{align*}
(3x + 3y)(x + y) - (x^2 + y^2) &= 3x^2 + 3xy + 3xy + 3y^2 - x^2 - y^2\\
&= 2x^2 + 6xy + 2y^2,
\end{align*}
which is greater than 1.  So we have
\begin{align*}
(3x^2 + 10xy + 3y^2) - (x^2 + y^2) + 1 &= (2x^2 + 6xy + 2y^2 - 1) + 2\\
&= 2(2x^2 + 3xy + 2y^2)\\
&= 2M.
\end{align*}
Therefore
\begin{align*}
2x^2 + 3xy + 2y^2 - M &= M - M\\
&= 0.
\end{align*}
</think> <answer>So the product $mM$ is $\boxed{0}.$</answer>
